==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tabulata
<hw>Tab`u*la"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
L. <ets>tabulatus</ets> floored.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An
artificial group of stony corals including those which have transverse
septa in the calicles. The genera <gen>Pocillopora</gen> and Favosites
are examples.</def> <-- ## note that Pocillopora is italicised but not
listed separately in this dictionary. Favosites is not italicised, and
has an entry as a headword. Is that the difference between italicisation
or not for genus names? -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tabulate</ent>⟦br⟧
